I"ú<h2 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>basmati rice</li>
  <li>water</li>
  <li>olive oil</li>
  <li>butter</li>
  <li>salt, pepper, other spices</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="method">Method</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Rinse the dry rice in a sieve under running water if preferred (I tend not to).</li>
  <li>Throw the desired amount of rice in a pot.</li>
  <li>For each cup of rice, add 1.5 cups of water.</li>
  <li>Add a generous splash of olive oil and a chunk of butter.</li>
  <li>Add salt, pepper and spices to preference.</li>
  <li>Get to a boil, put the lid on, and leave to simmer at low heat for 15 minutes.</li>
  <li>Turn off the heat and leave to simmer for a further 10 minutes.</li>
  <li>Take off the lid and fluff with a fork before serving.</li>
</ul>
